国家財政の抱える問題点と改革の方向性について根拠に基づいて議論できるようになることを目標とする。 細分化された到達目標は以下の通りである。 (1)公共部門が市場経済に介入すべき理論的枠組みの理解 (2)国の歳出がもたらす具体的な影響と介入手段への理解 (3)国の歳出における社会保障の仕組みへの理解 (4)租税システムと公平な運用に関する理解

Public finance of central government consists of annual income and annual expenditure. The former splits up into a tax and a public debt. The latter splits up into a public investment and a social security.

Traditional discussion on public finance was to suppress anti-democratic decision making process for a public investment. Now a days, for super-aged society like Japan, we should discuss a relationship between central governemt and local government.

The subdivided targets are as follows; 1) Understanding for the theoretical framework for a public sector intervention 2) Understanding for the effects and the tools of annual expenditure 3) Understanding for the social security system including a public pension, a heath insurance and so on 4) Understanding for the fair tax theory and system

